we show the summits of the High

00:23:08.350 --> 00:23:11.549
Tech Highs, because it
feels like so out of grasp.

00:23:11.549 --> 00:23:13.840
I think we have to make it
a little bit more accessible

00:23:13.840 --> 00:23:19.430
for the parental and teacher
communities around the country.

00:23:19.430 --> 00:23:23.200
The second thing I think we need
to do is think about policy,

00:23:23.200 --> 00:23:26.330
and the environment
into which we're

00:23:26.330 --> 00:23:29.240
making these transformations,
and maybe kick it

00:23:29.240 --> 00:23:31.532
to you for your story
about the architecture.

00:23:31.532 --> 00:23:32.490
MALE SPEAKER: Oh, yeah.

00:23:32.490 --> 00:23:36.580
We were talking before
the talk today--

00:23:36.580 --> 00:23:41.210
the idea that when you look at
a building, beautiful architect

00:23:41.210 --> 00:23:43.410
of a building, you
look at the building

00:23:43.410 --> 00:23:46.460
and you don't say I wonder
what kind of wrench they used.

00:23:46.460 --> 00:23:47.087
Right?

00:23:47.087 --> 00:23:48.420
Or what kind of drill they used.

00:23:48.420 --> 00:23:51.530
You talk about the actual
outcome of that building,

00:23:51.530 --> 00:23:54.040
and so our students are
that architect, the outcome.

00:23:54.040 --> 00:23:55.790
MICHAEL HORN: Yeah,
and I think the policy

00:23:55.790 --> 00:23:57.510
is concerned about the tools.

00:23:57.510 --> 00:23:59.150
