interact more with what

00:35:06.950 --> 00:35:08.500
they're being presented with.

00:35:08.500 --> 00:35:10.670
So I'm curious on two things.

00:35:10.670 --> 00:35:13.490
I'd love your thoughts
on like best practices

00:35:13.490 --> 00:35:14.760
around personalized learning.

00:35:14.760 --> 00:35:17.210
What do you think of
things like AltSchool--

00:35:17.210 --> 00:35:19.460
some of the folks who are
trying to solve that problem

00:35:19.460 --> 00:35:20.970
from a technology perspective.

00:35:20.970 --> 00:35:26.150
And then do you feel like a
focus on project-based learning

00:35:26.150 --> 00:35:28.790
is warranted, or is
there some other future

00:35:28.790 --> 00:35:31.800
that you imagine that
sort of around the curve

00:35:31.800 --> 00:35:36.380
that maybe we're not seeing
that's the next big thing or is

00:35:36.380 --> 00:35:38.570
there a more generalized
way to think about it?

00:35:38.570 --> 00:35:40.050
MICHAEL HORN: So I'm
really glad, first of all,

00:35:40.050 --> 00:35:41.820
that you separated those
two terms, because I think

00:35:41.820 --> 00:35:43.850
a lot of people they
hear student-centered or

00:35:43.850 --> 00:35:47.175
personalized and automatically
say that's 100% project based,

00:35:47.175 --> 00:35:48.800
and I don't think
that's actually true.

00:35:48.800 --> 00:35:49.300
Right?

00:35:49.300 --> 00:35:52.230
You don't learn to shoot
free throws in basketball

00:35:52.230 --> 00:35:54.690
in the game, you actually
have to practice them

00:35:54.690 --> 00:35:57.620
and it's not always
the most exciting.

00:35:57.620 --> 00:36:00.190
But you also play the game
to understand the context

00:36:00.190 --> 00:36:02.440
and build motivation
and apply, right?

00:36:02.440 --> 00:36:05.540
So there are give and
takes I think in education,

00:36:05.540 --> 00:36:10.490
and we've had this unbelievably
broken dialogue between "isms."

00:36:10.490 --> 00:36:13.780
You're either core knowledge
versus project-based learning,

00:36:13.780 --> 00:36:16.580
and it's like well,
hold on, I think

00:36:16.580 --> 00:36:18.380
there's actually value
in both and what's

00:36:18.380 --> 00:36:19.740
the right mix of things.

00:36:19.740 --> 00:36:22.170
And it turns out you do
need knowledge to know

00:36:22.170 --> 00:36:25.510
what to Google in learning,
and so that still is important,

00:36:25.510 --> 00:36:27.700
but so it too is applying it.

00:36:27.700 --> 00:36:31.520
So the way I think about
blended learning is it offers us

00:36:31.520 --> 00:36:33.930
the opportunity to
change the use of time

00:36:33.930 --> 00:36:36.880
so that we can break these
things that have been

00:36:36.880 --> 00:36:39.060
false dichotomies,
but I think has

00:36:39.060 --> 00:36:42.040
been very difficult like
in the time-based way

00:36:42.040 --> 00:36:44.600
we view schools to
actually do both.

00:36:47.989 --> 00:36:50.030
There's some great
project-based learning schools

00:36:50.030 --> 00:36:52.830
that are out there, but
there's some really bad ones

00:36:52.830 --> 00:36:54.860
where kids are doing
superficial things

00:36:54.860 --> 00:36:57.500
and they don't really understand
fundamentals underneath it,

00:36:57.500 --> 00:37:01.664
and so this is really the
opportunity to split that.

00:37:01.664 --> 00:37:03.580
So I'll answer that
question more directly now

00:37:03.580 --> 00:37:06.460
with just that preface, because
if you look at Summit Public

00:37:06.460 --> 00:37:10.240
Schools they are one that I
think is getting the mix right.

00:37:10.240 --> 00:37:12.200
On personalized
learning, really excited

00:37:12.200 --> 00:37:16.340
about a number of the
potentials coming around.

00:37:16.340 --> 00:37:19.030
I think there's a bit of
a split in the field right

00:37:19.030 --> 00:37:22.060
now around adaptive learning
engines versus a more

00:37:22.060 --> 00:37:24.650
playlist approach to the world.

00:37:24.650 --> 00:37:27.880
It's not clear to me what
is going to win there.

00:37:27.880 --> 00:37:30.910
I actually think
there's value in both,

00:37:30.910 --> 00:37:33.840
and I think the adaptive
learning is a way more complex

00:37:33.840 --> 00:37:39.580
problem than most people believe
it is because yes, you're

00:37:39.580 --> 00:37:41.080
getting way more
data from students,

00:37:41.080 --> 00:37:42.660
but they're also
sending a lot of signals

00:37:42.660 --> 00:37:44.451
based on what they ate
that morning that is

00:37:44.451 --> 00:37:47.450
very difficult to account for.

00:37:47.450 --> 00:37:50.010
So I think super
interesting place,

00:37:50.010 --> 00:37:52.080
really interested in what
Newton is doing, really

00:37:52.080 --> 00:37:54.209
interested in what
AltSchool is doing,

00:37:54.209 --> 00:37:56.750
really interested in what Khan
Academy is doing in that world

00:37:56.750 --> 00:37:59.240
as well, so lots of
interesting experiments.

00:37:59.240 --> 00:38:00.930
Really interested
also simultaneously

00:38:00.930 --> 00:38:03.624
on the playlist approach,
like Summit Public Schools

00:38:03.624 --> 00:38:05.540
is doing with their
personalized learning plan

00:38:05.540 --> 00:38:09.164
where there's 10 different
ways to learn a given standard

00:38:09.164 --> 00:38:11.080
and actually students
get to navigate and make

00:38:11.080 --> 00:38:12.280
those choices.

00:38:12.280 --> 00:38:15.850
And again, I think adaptability
versus assignability or choice

00:38:15.850 --> 00:38:18.060
will end up being a false
dichotomy in the future as

00:38:18.060 --> 00:38:18.559
well.

00:38:18.559 --> 00:38:23.330
I think there will be a mix
where just like Google helps

00:38:23.330 --> 00:38:25.730
nudge me, it doesn't
actually make decisions

00:38:25.730 --> 00:38:27.470
for me as I'm doing things.

00:38:27.470 --> 00:38:30.540
I think there will be something
with a trade-off and younger

00:38:30.540 --> 00:38:34.360
students you may give more
help making those decisions

00:38:34.360 --> 00:38:35.930
and do gradual
release as they get

00:38:35.930 --> 00:38:39.040
older so they become lifelong
learners and really owners

00:38:39.040 --> 00:38:41.330
of that learning experience.

00:38:41.330 --> 00:38:43.810
In terms of AltSchool
specifically,

00:38:43.810 --> 00:38:47.680
for those that don't know
just raised $100 million,

00:38:47.680 --> 00:38:54.026
I went to college with Max,
so I know him reasonably well.

00:38:54.026 --> 00:38:56.400
I'm really interest to see
what actually comes out of it.

00:38:56.400 --> 00:39:01.110
I think at minimum it'll be a
really exciting school network

00:39:01.110 --> 00:39:03.480
itself that helps
to disrupt a lot

00:39:03.480 --> 00:39:06.290
of independent or private
schools around the country.

00:39:06.290 --> 00:39:08.920
I think this micro-school
network is very exciting

00:39:08.920 --> 00:39:10.320
that's emerging.

00:39:10.320 --> 00:39:12.206
I think we might in
the future sort of

00:39:12.206 --> 00:39:15.630
see the Airbnb schooling
that allows for pop-ups

00:39:15.630 --> 00:39:17.550
and allows for very
different communities

00:39:17.550 --> 00:39:20.580
to form depending on
the day or what subject

00:39:20.580 --> 00:39:23.080
you're learning in the future.

00:39:23.080 --> 00:39:29.190
I'm skeptical of taking a
platform developed very deeply

00:39:29.190 --> 00:39:32.080
in a particular school setting
with a very particular model,

00:39:32.080 --> 00:39:35.267
and then just thinking, oh we'll
just give that to a district

00:39:35.267 --> 00:39:36.850
and it will work and
it will save them

00:39:36.850 --> 00:39:39.680
30% because they don't need
this administrative overhead

00:39:39.680 --> 00:39:40.660
or something like that.

00:39:40.660 --> 00:39:43.756
I'm very skeptical of that,
because it's interdependent,

00:39:43.756 --> 00:39:45.380
and I think that's
important right now.

00:39:45.380 --> 00:39:47.050
We're not ready
for modular stage,

00:39:47.050 --> 00:39:50.350
but I don't think it'll
just pour it over.

00:39:50.350 --> 00:39:53.270
Project-based learning-- I think
it's a deeper understanding

00:39:53.270 --> 00:39:57.430
of what projects can be and how
they interact with knowledge

00:39:57.430 --> 00:39:59.795
and things like that will
come down the pipeline,

00:39:59.795 --> 00:40:01.280
if that make sense.

00:40:01.280 --> 00:40:03.880
And I also think if we can
start to actually tie them

00:40:03.880 --> 00:40:06.850
into real world problems
increasingly that's maybe

00:40:06.850 --> 00:40:09.650
the next frontier where we
start to bring employers

00:40:09.650 --> 00:40:12.610
and experts in social capital
into these communities in very

00:40:12.610 --> 00:40:15.180
different ways from the ways
we've done traditionally.

00:40:15.180 --> 00:40:17.024
I think Google
can be a big part.

00:40:17.024 --> 00:40:18.690
AUDIENCE: I wonder
if it's almost better

00:40:18.690 --> 00:40:21.700
to think about intrinsic
versus extrinsic motivation

00:40:21.700 --> 00:40:25.230
as what you're trying to create
out of that system, as opposed

00:40:25.230 --> 00:40:27.942
to actually having
it be project-based.

00:40:27.942 --> 00:40:29.400
MICHAEL HORN: I
think that's right.

00:40:29.400 --> 00:40:33.660
I mean, it creates an excitement
and desire to know more,

00:40:33.660 --> 00:40:36.780
and also I didn't
know what engineering

00:40:36.780 --> 00:40:39.080
was until I was like
a junior in college,

00:40:39.080 --> 00:40:42.150
so a much better sense of
what real jobs and careers are

00:40:42.150 --> 00:40:43.262
out there.

00:40:43.262 --> 00:40:44.720
MALE SPEAKER: We
started with start

00:40:44.720 --> 00:40:47.670
the conversation by trying to
find blended learning, we can

00:40:47.670 --> 00:40:49.890
do the same thing with
personal learning,

00:40:49.890 --> 00:40:53.694
whether it's personal,
personalised, individualised or

00:40:53.694 --> 00:40:56.110
project-based learning and
what project-based learning is.

00:40:56.110 --> 00:40:57.910
I often get push-back
from students.

00:40:57.910 --> 00:41:00.870
I was speaking at ASU
with Dr. Crow in a class

00:41:00.870 --> 00:41:02.370
and one of the
student says, I don't

00:41:02.370 --> 00:41:03.786
want to do
project-based learning,

00:41:03.786 --> 00:41:06.620
because when I did project-based
learning when I was in school

00:41:06.620 --> 00:41:08.580
I was the one who
did all the work.

00:41:08.580 --> 00:41:10.630
And I'm like, you
didn't do project-based.

00:41:10.630 --> 00:41:13.650
You did one paper
