00:49:32.380 --> 00:49:35.820
I think one, the continued
improvement of the Chromebook

00:49:35.820 --> 00:49:40.010
platform at a price that
schools can embrace.

00:49:40.010 --> 00:49:41.840
Huge, because it
takes the equipment

00:49:41.840 --> 00:49:44.569
question off the table and
hopefully shifts the question

00:49:44.569 --> 00:49:45.610
to the learning question.

00:49:48.204 --> 00:49:49.620
And I've always
felt that with you

00:49:49.620 --> 00:49:53.300
is that you ask the
learning question first

00:49:53.300 --> 00:49:54.737
is the other really big thing.

00:49:54.737 --> 00:49:56.570
And I know you said the
pledge won't happen,

00:49:56.570 --> 00:49:59.842
but I think the more we
can get a conversation

00:49:59.842 --> 00:50:01.300
around the learning
questions we're

00:50:01.300 --> 00:50:03.470
trying to solve first,
really important.

00:50:03.470 --> 00:50:08.220
And then a lot of the apps
and the suite of tools

00:50:08.220 --> 00:50:12.390
that you can bring to bear,
regardless of platform

00:50:12.390 --> 00:50:15.620
quite frankly, but
showing again those things

00:50:15.620 --> 00:50:19.760
in service of the learning
goals just tremendous,

00:50:19.760 --> 00:50:21.740
but really make it about
the learning in each

00:50:21.740 --> 00:50:22.950
and every case.

00:50:22.950 --> 00:50:26.340
The other thing I'd love to see
Google do is think about you

00:50:26.340 --> 00:50:28.840
guys have thought a lot
about the learning registry

00:50:28.840 --> 00:50:32.110
and tagging open education
resources and things like that.

00:50:32.110 --> 00:50:34.660
I'd love to see more thought
about how assessments play

00:50:34.660 --> 00:50:37.010
into that, because
that's what will truly

00:50:37.010 --> 00:50:42.610
make learning content be useful
and come to life in a much more

00:50:42.610 --> 00:50:43.470
rich way.

00:50:43.470 --> 00:50:47.880
And I don't think we're
seeing enough innovation

00:50:47.880 --> 00:50:49.430
in that space.

